suncertify.db
Class DBSchema

java.lang.Object
  suncertify.db.DBSchema

public final class DBSchema
extends java.lang.Object

Represents the database record schema definition according to the written specification. The information in this uninstantiable utility class are independent of any database file.

Version:
1.0
Author:
Lars Kuettner

getFieldIndex

public static int getFieldIndex(java.lang.String fieldName)

Parameters:
fieldName - a string representing the field name whose index is to be determined
Returns:

getFieldName

public static java.lang.String getFieldName(java.lang.String fieldNameAnyCase)
Converts a field name given in arbitrary case letters, upper or lower, into the exact field name as specified as a constant string in this class, which then can be used to retrieve the field index.

Parameters:
fieldNameAnyCase - a string representing the case-insensitive field name whose case-sensitive equivalent is to be found
Returns:
a string representing the case-sensitive equivalent of the case-insensitive field name provided, or null if there is no match. The match is checked using equalsIgnoreCase.
